Author-Name:   Raman, Kalyan
Title: 
 Inductive Inference and Replications: A Bayesian Perspective.

Journal: Journal of Consumer Research
Pages: 633-43
Issue: 4
Volume: 20
Year: 1994
Month:  March 
Abstract:

 A probabilistic model is proposed to assess the value of replications.
 The corroboration of a theory is shown to be a function of the number of
 replications, the number of successful outcomes, and our initial beliefs.
 An adaptive control model provides the optimal policy for continuing
 replications, given the accumulated evidence for the theory, the precision
 deemed necessary, and the cost of replicating.


