Author-Name:   Vanden Abeele, Piet
Author-Name:  MacLachlan, Douglas L
Title: 
 Process Tracing of Emotional Responses to TV Ads: Revisiting the Warmth Monitor.

Journal: Journal of Consumer Research
Pages: 586-600
Issue: 4
Volume: 20
Year: 1994
Month:  March 
Abstract:

 Because of the transient nature of some emotions stimulated during TV
 commercials, measurement of emotional reactions at various points during
 an ad requires process tracing. This research discusses the analysis of
 process-tracing data using the Warmth Monitor as an illustration. We show
 that the establishment of the reliability and validity of process-tracing
 measures hinges on a suitable choice of the relevant domain of
 (co)variance in the data. The Warmth Monitor is shown to provide a
 reliable measure of warmth, but questions remain regarding the construct's
 meaning and valid measurement.


